This paper discusses recommendation systems and their effects on user behavior and preferences. It involves collaborative filtering methods and bias analysis, which are commonly studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact on user perceptions and inequalities, which could fall under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) or Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves quantifying and analyzing data, which could also fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
